<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 3/4. LH "33" root pos throughout. RH light thirds and fifths.
- Bars 1-6: first strophe G→Am→D→G. Bars 7-12: second strophe varied RH positions.
- Bridge bars 13-15: climax ascending d→e; Am→D7→G resolution.
- Dotted rhythms in bars 5, 10, 12 create rhythmic interest.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH bass line G→A→D→G forms root-movement arch in each strophe.
- RH ascends to G5 at bridge climax (bar 13-14) then resolves.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Light open 3/4; richer at bridge bars 13-14; gentle G close.
-->
